Description: irond is a IF-MAP MAP server
 irond is an experimental IF-MAP 2.0 compliant MAP server written in
 JAVA. irond supports both basic authentication and certificate-based
 authentication (using X.509 certificates) of MAP clients. irond is maintained
 by the Trust@HsH group at the Hochschule Hannover, initial development was
 carried out during the ESUKOM research project.
